1 families because of error in determining the number of expenditures
2 for medical care required of an individual or family as a condition
3 of eligibility, or payments where insufficient information is
4 available to confirm eligibility.
5 (iii) Payments, other than payments described in subparagraph
6 (i), for items and services furnished to an individual who is not
7 eligible for medical assistance under this state's plan or a waiver
8 of this state's plan with respect to the items and services, or
9 payments where insufficient information is available to confirm
10 eligibility.
11 (b) "Improper payment" means that term as defined in 31 USC
12 3351.
